<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Welltower (WELL)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Welltower Inc. — using FY2025 actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated March 18, 2026 · Data: FY2025 10-K</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${price.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{rev2025 !== null ? `$${(rev2025 / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">FY2025 Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{fcf2025 !== null ? `$${(fcf2025 / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{eps2025 !== null ? `$${eps2025}` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{rev2025 !== null && opInc2025 !== null ? `${((opInc2025 / rev2025) * 100).toFixed(1)}%` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash (Debt)</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Welltower generated <strong>${fcf2025 !== null ? fcf2025.toLocaleString() : 'N/A'} million</strong> in free cash flow in FY2025. This is operating cash flow minus capital expenditures. For REITs, operating cash flow (and AFFO) is heavily relied upon, but FCF shows real cash left after property upkeep and expansion.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>15% per year</strong> for 5 years. This accounts for strong demographic tailwinds (aging population) driving occupancy and rent growth in their senior housing operating (SHO) portfolio, along with accretive acquisitions.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>3.0% forever</strong>. This is standard for real estate, representing long-term inflation plus slight real growth. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>: Terminal Value = FCF₆ ÷ (discount rate − terminal growth rate).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>9%</strong> — our required rate of return (WACC). This reflects the current 10Y Treasury (4.18%) plus an equity risk premium, adjusted for Welltower's slightly lower beta typical of large-cap healthcare REITs.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash/Debt = Equity Value. Since Welltower is a REIT, it carries significant debt, so Net Cash is negative. Divide by shares outstanding ({shares}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">15%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Welltower is experiencing massive tailwinds in its Senior Housing Operating (SHO) segment due to the aging population and lack of new supply. High occupancy gains and rent increases justify a strong 15% growth rate as FCF accelerates.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">9%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury: 4.18%. REITs typically have lower betas than high-growth tech. A 9% required return is appropriate for a stable, dividend-paying, large-cap healthcare REIT with tangible real estate assets backing its cash flows.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">3.0%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Real estate cash flows naturally hedge against inflation. A 3% terminal growth rate assumes Welltower can continue to raise rents slightly above long-term inflation (~2-2.5%) into perpetuity, driven by demographics.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

